A personnel representative Of
the Agency for international De-
velopment will be in Phoenix
for two weeks, April 20 through
May /, to interview applicants
interested in secretarial posi-
lions overseas.


Assignments with AID are open
to young women with secretarial
experience and good shorthand
and tipping skills. The applicant
must be single, at least FL years
of age, an American citizen.
without dependents. and possess
excellent health and character.
Overseas appointments are for
two years in most posts.


These positions pay excellent
salaries, plus housing and other
benefits. including a differential
up to 25% of base salary, de-
pending on post.


The majority Of secretaries
are posted in headquarters in the
capital cities of such interesting
countries as Indonesia, Iran,

Turkey, Ethiopia. Nigeria. and
elsewhere in the Fart East, Near
East, and Africa. Positions are
also available in Washington. D.
G.


Interviews Will be conducted
by Mrs. Beulah W. Bean at the
Arizona State Employment Ser
vice, 207 E. Mcdowell Road,

Pour into well-greased custard
